<h1>Persons Home Page</h1>
<p>This is the home page. Here you will see a list of all the people. It might be empty now but as you add people it shall duly populate. It simply lists all the added people in the database, giving you a more user friendly way to view them. You should see
a person's name, surname, age, gender, income, email, postcode and msisdn.</p>

<table>
  <tr>
    <th>Name</th>
    <th>Surname</th>
    <th>Age</th>
    <th>Gender</th>
    <th>Income</th>
    <th>Email</th>
    <th>Postcode</th>
    <th>MSISDN</th>
  </tr>

<% @persons.each do |person| %>
  <tr>
    <td><%= person.name %></td>
    <td><%= person.surname %></td>
	<td><%= person.age %></td>
    <td><%= person.gender %></td>
	<td><%= person.income %></td>
    <td><%= person.email %></td>
    <td><%= person.postcode %></td>
    <td><%= person.msisdn %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Show', person %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Edit', edit_person_path(person) %></td>
    <td><%= link_to 'Destroy', person, :confirm => 'Are you sure?', :method => :delete %></td>
  </tr>
<% end %>
</table>

<p><%= link_to 'Add a new person', new_person_path %>


